               </t:location>
               <t:note>
                  <t:date type="foundation" notBefore="1500" notAfter="1550">1500-1550</t:date>
                  <t:desc type="foundation">The local tradition claims that the church was founded long ago, in the time of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8261Saaldob">King Saʿāldobā</t:persName>. The founder is unknown.
                     <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8265Sabagadi">Dağğāzmāč Sabāgādis</t:persName> re-established the church and donated gʷǝlt in the early <t:date>19th cent</t:date>.</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Dabr. The church of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7280Addigodana">ʿĀddigodānā Takla Hāymānot</t:placeName>, in the vicinity, was historically associated with Ḥarennat Māryām (but recently became an independent institution).
                     A ṣabal-source is located near <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC7280Addigodana">ʿĀddigodānā Takla Hāymānot</t:placeName>; near the source, there are ruins of the "old church of <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Haymanot</t:persName>".
</t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="description">
                     <t:figure>
                        <t:graphic url="Sites/MHG.tif">
                           <t:desc>The church photographed by Denis Nosnitsin during the Ethio-SPaRe project.</t:desc>
                        </t:graphic>
                     </t:figure>
                     22 Mss. photographed: <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg001">MHG-001</t:ref> "The Vita of Täklä Haymanot"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg002">MHG-002</t:ref> "The Homily of St. Michael"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg003">MHG-003</t:ref> "The Vita of Mänfäs Qǝddus"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg004">MHG-004</t:ref> "Four Gospels"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg005">MHG-005</t:ref> "The Homily of St. Michael"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg006">MHG-006</t:ref> "The Book of the Epistle"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg007">MHG-007</t:ref> "Pauline Epistles"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg008">MHG-008</t:ref> "The Book of the Funeral Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg009">MHG-009</t:ref> "The Book of the Chants"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg010">MHG-010</t:ref> "Collection of Marian prayers"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg011">MHG-011</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg012">MHG-012</t:ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg013">MHG-013</t:ref> "The Book of the Mistery"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg014">MHG-014</t:ref> "Miracles of Mary"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg015">MHG-015</t:ref> "The Book of the Baptismal Rite"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg016">MHG-016</t:ref> "The Homiliy of the Saviour of the world"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg017">MHG-017</t:ref> "Missal"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg018">MHG-018</t:ref> "Four Gospels"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg019">MHG-019</t:ref> "The Prayer of the Incense"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg020">MHG-020</t:ref> "Pauline Epistles"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg021">MHG-021</t:ref> "Miracles of Mary, other texts"; <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmhg022">MHG-022</t:ref> "1. The Book of Gǝṣṣǝw; 2. The Homily of the Sabbath of Christians"</t:ab>

                  <t:ab type="tabot">
                     <t:measure quantity="6"/>Tābots of <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10775Trinity">Trinity</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10581Zamika">ʾAragāwi</t:persName>,
                     <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">Mary</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4585Georgeo">George</t:persName>,
                     <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS1284Abrehaa">ʾAbrǝha and ʾAṣbǝḥa</t:persName>,
                     <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS12538PeterPaul">Peter and Paul</t:persName> (some of them are said to be marble tabots).</t:ab>
               </t:note>
